@article{ISI:000455968200011,
	Abstract = {{The photophysical properties of the compound
   {[}(ThiaSO(2))(Mn-II)(2)(DMF)(4)(H2O)(2)] (2), ThiaSO(2) =
   p-tert-butylsulfonylcalix{[}4]arene, are presented and compared to the
   ones of {[}(ThiaSO(2))(2)(Mn-II)(4)F]K (1). The orange luminescence of 2
   is attributed, as for 1, to the Mn-II centred T-4(1)->(6)A(1) transition
   and shows, for this type of complex, the weak influence of the Mn2+
   coordination and ThiaSO(2) conformation on this luminescence, the
   temperature and pressure dependence and quenching by molecular dioxygen
   of which are reported for 2. The latter is attributed to energy transfer
   from the T-4(1) state exciting dioxygen to its (1)sigma(+)(g) state and
   is responsible for the photosynthesis of the
   {[}(ThiaSO(2))(Mn-III)(DMF)(2)]Na (3) complex in DMF solution from 1 or
   2. This reaction was studied by UV/Visible and EPR spectroscopy. The
   molecular structure and EPR spectroscopy of 3 are also presented.}},
