@article{ISI:000433403800028,
	Abstract = {{Fifteen heptamethine dyes in which a tricyanofuran acceptor is linked to
   donors of different strengths were synthesized, and their absorption,
   thermal, electrochemical, and second-order nonlinear optical properties
   were investigated. While the variation of the peripheral bulky
   substituents allowed a decrease of the intermolecular interactions in
   the solid state, subtle engineering of the heterocyclic donor provided
   dyes with electronic structures that varied between dipolar and
   cyanine-like (i.e., with little bond length alternation and with ground
   and excited states having similar dipole moment) and remarkably high
   quadratic hyperpolarizabilities (mu beta(1.9)) of up to 115 000 x
   10(-48) esu.}},
