@article{ISI:000428530600014,
	Abstract = {{A new family of three Dy-III mononuclear complexes and one DyIII chain
   system based on the same ligand
   {[}1,3-di(pyridin-4-yl)propane-1,3-dione] has been isolated as single
   crystals. By varying the synthesis conditions, it has been possible to
   finely control the number of ligands coordinated to the central
   lanthanide atom (from 1 to 3) and then the total charge of the complex
   unit (from +2 to neutral), as well as the local geometry around the
   Dy-III ion (from D-4d to D-2d). The magnetic properties of the four
   complexes have been studied and rationalized by ab initio calculations
   to illustrate the correlation between the metal-ion environment, due to
   the number of coordinated ligands, and their SMM behaviours.}},
