@article{ISI:000384529800002,
	Abstract = {{The ligand exchange in (n-Bu4N)(2)(OsCl6)-Cl-IV (n-Bu4N =
   tetra-n-butylammonium) leads to the formation of the osmium(IV)
   heptacyanide, the first fully inorganic homoleptic complex of
   heptacoordinated osmium. The single-crystal X-ray diffraction (SC-XRD)
   study reveals the pentagonal bipyramidal molecular structure of the
   {[}Os(CN)(7)](3-) anion. The latter being a diamagnetic analogue of the
   highly anisotropic paramagnetic synthon, {[}ReIV(CN)(7)](3-) can be used
   for the synthesis of the model heterometallic coordination compounds for
   the detailed study and simulation of the magnetic properties of the
   low-dimensional molecular nanomagnets involving 5d metal heptacyanides.}},
